# Data Input Boundaries

All external data enters through three doors: phone messages, email parsing, or scheduled triggers. Every door feeds the same queue.

## Input Patterns by Domain

| Domain      | Input method                         | Explicitly excluded                                        |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| Calendar    | Email parsing + conversational input | Google Calendar API, tsdav, any external calendar API      |
| School      | Email parsing + conversational input | Canvas, Google Classroom, any LMS API                      |
| Finances    | Email parsing + conversational input | Plaid, any bank/financial API                              |
| Travel      | Email parsing + conversational input | FlightAware, AeroAPI, any flight/booking API               |
| Business    | Email parsing + conversational input | HoneyBook, Dubsado, 17hats, any external CRM               |
| Meals       | Conversational input                 | Spoonacular, Edamam, any recipe/meal planning API          |
| Maintenance | Conversational input                 | CarFax, HomeZada, any vehicle/home maintenance service API |

## Business CRM

Business lead tracking uses an internal CRM schema owned by the topic profile — not an external CRM service. The schema covers: lead contact, inquiry date, event details, pipeline stage, follow-up history, and booking status. Each entity with a service business gets a profile; leads are scoped to their owner.

## Calendar Serving

The system serves a local CalDAV endpoint that calendar apps subscribe to — accessible off-network via the ngrok tunnel. Calendar data enters via email parsing (appointment confirmations, .ics attachments) or conversational input — never by consuming an external calendar API.

## Principle

When considering a new data source, the answer is always: parse it from email, accept it via conversation, or build a local adapter that feeds the queue. Never add a paid third-party API without explicit discussion.
